docs.abstract: Google is becoming more public about its data centers, talking about its network and how much fiber it owns. The idea is to show off assets that Amazon, Microsoft and IBM cannot match in the competition for cloud customers.
docs.snippet: Google is becoming more public about its data centers, talking about its network and how much fiber it owns. The idea is to show off assets that Amazon, Microsoft and IBM cannot match in the competition for cloud customers.
docs.lead_paragraph: Google is wielding a new weapon against Amazon and Microsoft for cloud computing customers: itself.

headline.main: Google Is Its Own Secret Weapon in the Cloud
headline.print_headline: Google Sells Users on Cloud Computing

docs.abstract: If you’re up on big data, you’ve heard of something called Hadoop. It may be worth billions, but some of Hadoop’s biggest backers look like they are moving on from it.
docs.snippet: If you’re up on big data, you’ve heard of something called Hadoop. It may be worth billions, but some of Hadoop’s biggest backers look like they are moving on from it.
docs.lead_paragraph: There is increasing evidence that Hadoop — one of the most important technologies of the past several years for big data analysis —is not keeping up with the world that created it.

headline.main: Companies Move On From Big Data Technology Hadoop

docs.abstract: IBM plans to invest heavily in accelerating the adoption of the open-source big data software, Spark. With the move, IBM is investing as much in its own future as in the open-source project.
docs.snippet: IBM plans to invest heavily in accelerating the adoption of the open-source big data software, Spark. With the move, IBM is investing as much in its own future as in the open-source project.
docs.lead_paragraph: The IBM “endorsement effect” has often shaped the computer industry over the years. In 1981, when IBM entered the personal computer business, the company decisively pushed an upstart technology into the mainstream.

headline.main: IBM Invests to Help Open-Source Big Data Software — and Itself
